10 Effective use of illustrations . “ Jesus spoke to the crowds by illustrations , ” we are told . “ Indeed , without an illustration he would not speak to them . ” ( Matthew 13 :34 ) We can not help but marvel at his matchless ability to teach profound truths through everyday things . Farmers planting seeds , women preparing to bake bread , children playing in the marketplace , fishermen hauling in nets , shepherds searching for lost sheep—these were things his listeners had seen many times . When important truths are tied in with familiar things , such truths are etched quickly and deeply on the mind and heart .—Matthew 11 :16-19 ; 13 :3-8 , 33 , 47-50 ; 18 :12-14 .
