11 Jehovah also provided a truly remarkable demonstration of his protective power when he transferred the life of his only-begotten Son to the womb of the Jewish virgin Mary . An angel told Mary that she would “ conceive in [ her ] womb and give birth to a son . ” The angel explained : “ Holy spirit will come upon you , and power of the Most High will overshadow you . ” ( Luke 1 :31 , 35 ) Seemingly , God ’ s Son had never been so vulnerable . Would the sin and imperfection of the human mother blemish the embryo ? Would Satan be able to injure or kill that Son before He was born ? Impossible ! Jehovah formed , in effect , a protective wall around Mary so that nothing—no imperfection , no hurtful force , no murderous human , nor any demon—could damage the growing embryo , from the moment of conception on . Jehovah continued to protect Jesus during his youth . ( Matthew 2 :1-15 ) Until God ’ s appointed time , his dear Son was unassailable .
