Scientists say that we develop a special sense called proprioception , which is the body ’ s sense of its own orientation and the placement of the limbs . For example , this sense enables you to clap your hands with your eyes closed . One adult patient who lost her proprioception was unable to stand , walk , or even sit up as a result .
